The SpyCloud App for Splunk pulls data from the SpyCloud Enterprise API.

# Support: #
- Splunk 6.5, 6.6, 7.0, 7.1


# Installation: #
1. After installing this app restart Splunk.
2. On the Splunk home page click on the gear icon. This will take you to the Manage Apps page.
3. Then go to Manage Apps and find the 'SpyCloud' app. Click on 'Settings' and enter your API key.


# Data Population: #
- Data populated every hour. Once you install the app the dashboards will be empty until the input runs.
- The inputs will pull data from the SpyCloud API and add the data to two new Source types:
'spycloud_breach_catalog' and 'spycloud_watchlist'


# Setup Page: #
- The bare minimum requirement is to have a working SpyCloud API key.
- The alerts "SpyCloud - Compromised Active User Alert" and "SpyCloud - Compromised Active User Alert - Admin"
are disabled by default. If you do not have LDAP data to query against leave them disabled.
as the alerts will never fire without the additional LDAP data. A notification in the UI is also provided.
- If this app is installed on Splunk Cloud, a separate notification will display on the set up page informing
the user that LDAP queries will not work on a Cloud Environment.


# Features: #
- Breached Asset Types
- Breach Exposure Timeline
- Breach Catalog
- Email Watchlist Assets
- Domain Watchlist Assets


# Pre-built Panels available: #
The following pre-built panels are available to use on your own dashboards. By default the searches run over the last
30 days, but you can override this:
- active_employees_in_breach_data
- breach_catalog
- breach_exposure_timeline
- domain_watchlist_assets
- email_watchlist_assets
- your_breached_asset_types


# Pulling in LDAP Data (Optional): #
- The purpose of pulling in LDAP data is to enrich the breach data collected from SpyCloud. This allows
you to pull in Employee information related to email addresses associated with a breach.
- In order to pull in LDAP data you will need the Splunk Supporting Add-on for Active Directory
(https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/1151/) set up and configured
- This feature will not work on a Splunk Cloud environment.


# Saved searches: #
- SpyCloud Breach Catalog Lookup Populator
    This search automatically maintains a lookup filled with breach catalog data.
    It is used by the app's dashboard panels.
- SpyCloud Active User Lookup Populator
    This search maintains a lookup of active LDAP users. Does not function if LDAP is not configured
    (see the "Pulling in LDAP Data" section).
- SpyCloud - Compromised Active User Alert
    In the case of an active user becoming compromised, this will alert that user by e-mail.
- SpyCloud - Compromised Active User Alert - Admin
    In the case of an active user becoming compromised, this will alert the configured administrator by e-mail.


# Prerequisites: #
     If using the LDAP functionality of this app, Splunk Supporting Add-on for Active Directory is needed.
     Otherwise this app has no additional dependencies. This app does use the open source "requests" library,
     though it ships with Splunk so no configuration needs to be done by the end user.


# Release Notes: #
v. 0.4.5
- Added validation check for API credentials on setup page
- Setup page now requires you to be an admin role to access it

v. 0.4.4
- Added Attribution for text.js to README
- Email validation added to setup page.

v. 0.4.3
- Fixed bug where scripted input was not accounting for JSON being unordered.
- Notification provided on setup page for the following scenarios:
  - You do not have 'Splunk Supporting Add-on for Active Directory' installed or you are on cloud which cannot have
  the Add-on installed.
- Changes to Main dashboard:
  - Top numbers open new panels that show Breach Asset Details for Emails, Usernames, IP Addresses, and Infected Users.
  - Color-coded severity has been added for Breach Assets.
- Changes to Watchlist dashboard:
  - Domains and Email Watchlists have been modified to utilize the watchlist/identifiers endpoint.
  - 'Active Employees Who Show Up in Breach Data' panel will show a Notice if no results are found asking if the
  'Splunk Supporting Add-on for Active Directory' app was installed and configured.
- Prebuilt panels have been updated to reflect changes to Watchlist and Breach Assets


# Troubleshooting: #
- On initial run of the input, do not restart Splunk until all data has been onboarded, otherwise you may end up with
duplicate results.


# Support: #
- Support for this app is provided through e-mail during weekday business hours (US, Central Time).
- Please send your questions/concerns to support@spycloud.com.


